generated_description: la bahia antiques is an antique show and sale held annually in burton, texas, as part of the round top antique festival. established in 1992 by burton native roy schmidt and his wife carol, along with their daughters carrie and courtney, the event features over 70 dealers offering a wide range of american and english furniture, flow blue, sterling silver, clocks, european linens, books, primitives, american stoneware, vintage and estate jewelry, architectural items, elegant glass, vintage and repurposed items, and collectibles. the show is held in the historic 1879 la bahia dance hall and community center and is known for its consistent quality and free admission, with no cover charge. the festival is held twice a year, in the spring and fall, and attracts visitors from across texas and the country.
